This paper deals with the computation of expected predictions in machine learning models, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on probabilistic circuits, which are commonly used in machine learning models for classification and regression tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of expected predictions in handling missing data during prediction time, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and social impact (cs.SI) applications. Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely candidates.
